[{"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Oberfinanzdirektion M\u00fcnster S-2225a - 165 - St 12 - 31 S-2225aEStG: 10eEStG: 10e / 1EStG: 10e / 2EStG: 10e / 4EStG: 10e / 5aEStG: 10e / 6EStG: 10e / 6aEStG: 7EStG: 7 / 5EStG: 7 / : 7 / 5aEStG: 7bEStG: 10EStG: 10bEStG: 10dEStG: 21aEStG: 34fEStG: 52 / 21EStDV: 82bEStDV: 82hEStDV: 82kEStR: 43EStR: 44EStR: 54EStR: 157AO / 1: 312 / 2AO: 165AO: 39 / 2AO: 165 : 17BGB: 812BGB: 951BdF IV b 3 - S-2225a - 115/90 v"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "25 10 1990 BStBl 1990 I 626 (coord"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "State decree) Questions of doubt about the application of the Home Ownership Promotion Act of 15 5 1986 (BStBl I page 278) Reference: Circular decrees of 18 11 1988 (ESt-Nr: 59/1988), 27 6 1989 (ESt-Nr: 54/1989) and 7 9 1987 (ESt-Nr 68/1987) S-2225a - 154 - St 16 - 31I Acquisition / construction of an apartment used for own residential purposes on a heritable building plotII Buildings on third-party land: III Apartment in one's own house - decisive point in timeIV Extensions and extensionsV Subsequent production costs in the case of partially paid acquisition VI Subsequent propertyVII \u00a7 10e EStG for owner associationsVIII \u00a7 10e Para 6 EStGIX Debt interest deduction according to \u00a7 10e Para 6 a EStGX Depreciation in cases of mixed or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Changed useXI Waiver of the value-in-use taxationXII Equity measuresXIII Tax treatment of building society savings interest"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Order of 18 11 1988 revised and updated"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "The orders of 18 11 1988 27 6 1989 and 7 9 1987 are hereby repealed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "I would ask you to include a corresponding note in the procurement instructions"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "The general regulations on No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "I \"Acquisition or manufacturing costs i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "\u00a7 10e EStG \"does not apply, as corresponding instructions are contained in the BMF letter of 25 October 1990 (BStBl 1990 I page 626 Appendix 19 to the manual edition of the ESt 1990; hereinafter: BMF letter) and in the ESt guidelines 1990 (hereinafter: EStR)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "I Acquisition / construction of an apartment used for own residential purposes on a heritable building plot of land Leasehold interest, which the person entitled to leasehold pays to the property owner for the continued use of the heritable building plot, can be deducted as special expenses up to the beginning of the first use of the apartment in accordance with Section 10e (6) EStG, insofar as they are to the time before the start of first use (Sect. 52 i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Section 50 of the BMF letter)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Ground rent that is paid for periods of time after moving into the apartment can only be taken into account for tax purposes within the framework of Section 10e (6a) of the Income Tax Act"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "A deduction as a permanent burden i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "\u00a7 10 Paragraph 1 No. 1 a EStG is ruled out (BFH judgment of 24 10 1990 BStBl 1991 II page 175)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "The development costs accepted by a leaseholder as agreed and paid before the apartment is used for the first time can be deducted in full as special expenses in accordance with Section 10e (6) EStG, if the legally effective conclusion of the leasehold contract or the contract aimed at the transfer of a leasehold right before the 1st 1992 lies (BMF letter of 16 12 1991 BStBl I page 1011)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "If, in these old cases, the leaseholder has only paid the development costs after moving into the owner-occupied apartment or if the corresponding leasehold contract or the contract for the transfer of a leasehold was concluded after December 31, 1991, these can only be taken into account for tax purposes in accordance with Section 10e (6) EStG, than they are attributable to the period before self-use begins (see re 3)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "The acquisition costs for a heritable building right cannot be taken into account within the framework of Section 10e Paragraph 2 and Paragraph 2 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "In particular, they are not to be included in the assessment basis according to Section 10e, Paragraph 1, since the legislature has expressly only favored half of the acquisition costs for the land"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "The expenses of a leaseholder for the acquisition of the leasehold can therefore not be equated with the acquisition costs of a property owner for the land"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "The assessment base according to \u00a7 10e EStG does not include the capitalized value of the ground rent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "The acquisition costs for the heritable building right can be taken into account in accordance with Section 10e, Paragraph 6 of the Income Tax Act (Section 52 of the BMF letter), provided they are attributable to the time before moving into the apartment."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "II Buildings on third-party land: The right to deduct within the meaning of Section 10e EStG is, according to Section 5 of the BMF letter of 25 October 1990, the civil or beneficial owner (Section 39 (2) No. 1 Tax Code) who is responsible for the manufacturing or Has borne acquisition costs"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "The prerequisites for the acceptance of beneficial ownership by the builder are usually not met in the case of buildings on third-party land (see section 6 of the BMF letter of 25 October 1990; BFH judgment of 21 May 1992 BStBl II, page 944)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "If, however, a heritable building right or a usufructuary right has been ordered for the building owner on the undeveloped property, the building owner acquires civil rights ownership of the building he has built"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "According to \u00a7 39 Paragraph 2 No. 1 Sentence 1 AO, beneficial ownership only exists if someone other than the owner exercises actual control over an asset in such a way that he usually excludes the owner from affecting the asset for the normal useful life can"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "The mere fact that the beneficial owner erects a building on a property made available to him and bears the burden of the property does not constitute beneficial ownership of the user (BFH judgment of 21 December 1978 BStBl 1979 Part II, page 466)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Even the mere consent of the owner to the building project does not constitute economic ownership of the client"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Rather, it is necessary that the owner is permanently excluded from affecting the property by contractual agreements or for other reasons"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "This requirement is fulfilled if the right to surrender of the civil legal owner no longer has any economic significance, or if there is no longer any claim to surrender at all (BFH judgment of 21 12 1978 and BFH judgment of 21 5 1992)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "As a rule, these prerequisites are only met by the person entitled to permanent residence within the meaning of Section 31 et seq. Housing Promotion Act (WEG), provided that their rights and obligations, from an economic point of view, correspond to the rights and obligations of an owner and that they receive appropriate compensation on the basis of the permanent residence contract upon termination of the right of residence (Section 7 of the BMF letter)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "For details, see II 3. Rights to use an apartment based on real or contractual obligations do not constitute beneficial ownership"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "The usufructuary with reservation is also not to be regarded as the beneficial owner of the built apartment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "As a rule, an apartment is also acquired within the meaning of \u00a7 10e EStG if it was created by building work on the part of the person entitled to use it on third-party land and the owner of the property in exchange for his claim for expenses and compensation in connection with \u00a7 951 BGB \u00a7 812 BGB (see Sections 1 and 15 of the BMF letter)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "With the transfer of the property, the claim for expenses and compensation ceases to exist under civil law"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "An express declaration by the contracting parties about the treatment of the expense and compensation claim is therefore not required"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Acquisition costs of the building are now present in the amount of the lost expenditure and compensation claim"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "It can be assumed that the estimated amount of the expense and compensation claim corresponds to the amount of the manufacturing costs borne by the taxpayer (Section 15 of the BMF letter)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "These production costs are not to be reduced by fictitious or possibly drawn depreciation amounts in the meantime"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "The acquisition costs are entirely attributable to the building without the associated land (section 17 sentence 2 of the BMF letter)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "The waiver of the claim for expenses and compensation is thus comparable to the payment of a fee; its amount serves as the assessment basis for the deduction amount according to \u00a7 10e EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "However, the tax relief under Section 10e EStG can only be used for the assessment period in which ownership, uses, encumbrances and risks of the property are transferred to the taxpayer"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "A waiver of the claim for expenses and compensation without transfer of ownership is not sufficient"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Example: S has been living in one of the apartments in his parents' two-family house for free since 1987"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "In 1988 he extended his apartment with the consent of his parents at his own expense for 50,000 DM"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "In 1991, the taxpayers agreed that the property should be transferred to the son in return for payment of the expenses and compensation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "However, ownership, benefits and encumbrances of the property do not pass to the son until 1992"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Solution: By adding to the apartment he used himself, the son acquired a claim for expenses and compensation in accordance with Section 951 in conjunction with Section 812 of the German Civil Code (BGB) in the amount of DM 50,000"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "A consideration of the expenses according to \u00a7 10e EStG is not yet possible because the son has neither become the civil nor the economic owner of the extension"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "For the assessment period 1991, a tax relief according to \u00a7 10e EStG is also out of the question, as the taxpayer has waived the claim for expenses and compensation, but has not yet established any civil-legal ownership of the property"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "With the transfer of the property in 1992, the acquisition costs of the building are now in the amount of the lost expenditure and compensation claim in the amount of DM 50,000"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "These acquisition costs relate entirely to the building without the associated land"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "However, since the present case is a two-family house, the acquisition costs are to be distributed over the two apartments in proportion to the usable area"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "It is true that the taxpayer's construction work did not create a new apartment, as is expressly requested in the BMF letter"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "This is merely an apartment extension that is favored according to Section 10e Paragraph 2 EStG, but the claim for reimbursement of expenses is to be treated as an acquisition expense in the course of the transfer of ownership of the building, with the result that it is a purchase transaction according to Section 10e Paragraph 1 Clause 4 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "The period between the completion of the construction work and the subsequent transfer of ownership is also irrelevant"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Funding under Section 10e EStG is to be refused if, upon completion of the construction work before the assessment period 1987, the tax relief under Section 7b EStG would have been claimed (cf. BMF letter of 4 7 1986 BStBl Part I, page 318 ff), because this would lead to double funding for one and the same construction project"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "According to Section 7 of the BMF letter, the person entitled to permanent residence within the meaning of Section 31 ff"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "As a rule, WEG is to be regarded as the beneficial owner of the apartment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "The prerequisite, however, is that the taxpayer has signed a corresponding model legal contract for permanent residence under \u00a7 31 ff"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "WEG completes"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Through this model contract, the person entitled to permanent residency is to achieve a position that equates him economically with an apartment owner"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Permanent right of residence can be granted to an existing building or a building that is yet to be constructed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "The right of residence can be concluded for an unlimited period as well as for a particularly long period of time"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "If the right of residence is to correspond to the model contract, the following requirements must be met: It must in any case be alienable and inheritable"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "In the event of a premature termination of the permanent right of residence, the property owner must pay the person entitled to permanent residence an appropriate compensation in the amount of the market value of the permanent right of residence"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "After the expiry of the permanent right of residence, the owner is obliged to procure residential property for those entitled to permanent residence against the cancellation of the permanent right of residence"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "For this purpose, a notarial notice of conveyance must be provided in the land register when the permanent right of residence is concluded"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "If the person entitled to permanent residence assumes the financing of the purchase of the property and the building equipment as well as the interest and repayment of the borrowed capital as well as the ongoing management costs, he is to be regarded as the beneficial owner (BFH judgment of 22 October 1985 Federal Tax Gazette 1986 Part II page 258)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "The assessment basis of \u00a7 10e EStG includes the acquisition costs for the long-term right of residence or the production costs borne by the person entitled to permanent residence"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "The costs for the land are to be excluded from the assessment base in any case"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Example: S is granted permanent right of residence for the upper apartment in a two-family house"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "In return for the granting of permanent residence rights, S waives the repayment of a loan claim due from the property owner in the amount of DM 200,000"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Solution: Since S spends an amount of DM 200,000 on granting permanent residence rights, he is to be regarded as the beneficial owner of the upper apartment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "He can therefore take advantage of the tax relief under Section 10e EStG for the acquisition costs of DM 200,000"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Example: The parents of the S allow him to build an apartment by adding another storey to their family house"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "S carried out the construction work on its own account in 1990 with a total expenditure of 150,000 DM"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "After completion of the construction work in 1991, the parents grant the S permanent right of residence in the apartment he has built with a contract certified by a notary"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Solution: S can claim the support of \u00a7 10e EStG for the apartment completed in 1991"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "The assessment basis within the meaning of Section 10e EStG is the production costs incurred by him in the amount of DM 150,000"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "If, in the case of a construction project on third-party land, a permanent right of residence is granted immediately afterwards, a preliminary cost deduction is generally possible in accordance with Section 10e (6) of the Income Tax Act"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "If the taxpayer has already moved into the apartment at the time the permanent right of residence is granted, he can claim the preliminary cost deduction in accordance with Section 10e (6) EStG up to the point in time at which he has become the beneficial owner of the apartment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "III Apartment in one's own house - relevant point in time According to section 8 of the BMF letter of 15 5 1987 (BStBl 1987 I page 434), the actual design at the time of moving into the apartment used for one's own residential purposes was decisive for the tax reduction under Section 10e EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "In this respect, there was a change compared to the existing regulation under Section 7b of the Income Tax Act, according to which the design at the time of manufacture or acquisition must be taken into account when determining the beneficiary property (Section 54 Paragraph 1 Clause 4 EStR 1987)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Section 9 of the BMF letter of 25 October 1990 does not contain any corresponding regulation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Now, when applying Section 10e EStG, a separate check must be made for each assessment period to determine the amount of acquisition / production costs for the owner-occupied apartment in the sense of valuation law"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Example: A purchases a two-family house in the 1988 calendar year for DM 400,000 plus DM 100,000 for the land"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "He moves into the ground floor apartment in the same calendar year, the upper floor apartment is initially rented"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "After the tenant moved out in 1990, A converted the house into a single-family house and used it for his own residential purposes"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Solution: In the calendar years 1988 and 1989, A can benefit from tax incentives in accordance with Section 10e (1) EStG in the amount of 5 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "deduct from 225,000 DM (1/2 of 400,000 DM plus 1/4 of 100,000 DM) for the owner-occupied ground floor apartment as special expenses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "From the assessment period 1990 to 1995, the deduction amount according to \u00a7 10e EStG in the amount of 5 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "of 300,000 DM (maximum assessment basis) can be taken into account to reduce tax"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "IV Extensions and extensions Because of the terms extension and extension, reference is made to Section 17 of the II Housing Act (WoBauG) (BStBl 1990 I page 424 and Annex 3 EStR 1990)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "An expansion i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Section 17 (1) II WoBauG and Section 10e (2) EStG are also to be assumed if previous ancillary or accessory rooms are structurally converted into (main) living spaces in the narrower sense using significant construction costs (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Expansion of a basement room into a children's room)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Considerable construction costs are to be assumed here if the construction costs incurred are at least 1/3 of the costs that would be proportionately attributable to corresponding living spaces if the building were assumed to be new"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Modifications to an apartment only lead to extensions i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Section 10e EStG, if the living spaces were unsuitable for residential purposes due to the change in living conditions"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "It is not sufficient that the living spaces were in need of repair (BFH judgment of April 28, 1992 BStBl 1992 Part II, page 823)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "The requirements of Section 10e (2) EStG are also met when a taxpayer first builds ancillary and accessory rooms to the owner-occupied apartment (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "a laundry room, storage or drying room)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "In any case, the expansion or expansion must be carried out in a spatial context with the owner-occupied apartment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "It is sufficient if, after completion, both the extension or the extension and the apartment itself are used (Section 11 of the BMF letter)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Example: A acquires a two-family house in the 1990 calendar year free of charge in anticipated succession, the upper floor apartment of which is rented"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "After building an extension to the two-family house at a price of 100,000 DM, he moved into the ground floor apartment in 1992 after completion"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "The same-sized part of the extension located on the upper floor will be rented out after completion"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Solution: A can deduct a deduction amount of 5 percent from the assessment period 1992 in accordance with \u00a7 10e EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "of the pro rata production costs of 50,000 DM = 2,500 DM"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "The expenses incurred for the rented part are to be included as subsequent production costs in the depreciation assessment basis"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Manufacturing costs for an expansion or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "An extension to a single-family house used for one's own residential purposes, for which the increased deductions according to \u00a7 7b EStG by way of the \"small transitional regulation\" (\u00a7 52 para 2 EStG must be taken into account (section 32 sentence 2 of the BMF letter; confirmed by BFH judgment of October 4, 1990 BStBl 1991 II page 221)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "However, the taxpayer regularly has the option of waiving the unused deduction amounts according to Section 7b EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "This can be advantageous in individual cases if the possible application of Section 10e Paragraph 2 EStG results in a higher tax reduction in accordance with Section 34f Paragraph 2 or 3 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Manufacturing costs for an expansion or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "An extension of an apartment used for own residential purposes that falls under the \"Large Transitional Regulation\" (Section 52 (21) sentence 2 EStG) and for which the taxpayer has not yet waived the value-in-use taxation, cannot benefit under Section 10e (2) EStG (Section 4 of the BMF letter)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Rather, the production costs increase the depreciation assessment basis of the owner-occupied apartment, at the same time the rental value for the newly created living space must be recorded (BFH judgment of 5 8 1992 X R 23/92 DStZ 92 S"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "768)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "It can therefore be more favorable in individual cases if the taxpayer waives the \"Large Transitional Regulation\" and takes advantage of the tax relief under Section 10e (2) EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Is in the expansion or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "If a new apartment is built through the extension, the taxpayer's expenses can only be subsidized in accordance with Section 10e (1) EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "In this respect, no expansion or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "No extension given to an apartment used for own residential purposes (judgment of the FG M\u00fcnster dated 20 10 1992 Az 6 K 5468/89 E, not published)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Example: In 1989 A acquires a building for commercial purposes free of charge"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "In the course of the 1989 calendar year, A had a kitchen connection, a bath / toilet, a shower and a staircase built into this building"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "In addition, expenses were incurred for re-covering the roof (no changes to the roof construction)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "The existing building is being redesigned using the foundations and the load-bearing parts (interior and exterior walls) and has been used by A for its own residential purposes since 1 5 1990"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "The construction costs incurred by A in this connection amount to DM 105,000"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Solution: A did not create a new building due to the construction work carried out (Section 2 of the BMF letter of 17 2 1992 BStBl Part I, page 115)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Nevertheless, in the present case, A receives the basic subsidy according to \u00a7 10e Abs 1 EStG because he has built an apartment in his own house (assessment basis DM 105,000)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "The expenses favored according to \u00a7 10e Abs 2 EStG do not include the proportional costs for the land (section 12 sentence 3 of the BMF letter)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "The use of the tax breaks according to \u00a7 34f EStG i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Section 10e (2) EStG is in the case of an extension i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Section 17 (2) II WoBauG or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "in the case of an extension of the top floor by the end of 1991, it does not depend on the amount of the expenses borne by the property owner"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "They are to be granted even if the tax reduction according to \u00a7 34f EStG already exceeds the construction costs"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "A limitation of the tax relief according to \u00a7 34f EStG was introduced for the first time by the Tax Amendment Act 1992 of 25 2 1992 (cf. order of 5 3 1992 - S-2225a - 165 - St 12 - 31)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "According to Section 34f (4) sentence 1 EStG, the taxpayer can only claim the Baukindergeld up to the amount of the assessment basis of the deductible amounts according to Section 10e (1) or 2 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "This limitation applies for the first time to objects that were acquired or manufactured in the assessment period 1992"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "V Subsequent production costs in the case of partially paid acquisition In the case of a partially paid acquisition, the acquisition process is divided into a paid and a free part according to the ratio of the fee to the market value of the entire asset"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "The ancillary acquisition costs are not taken into account in this ratio determination"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Rather, they are later to be added directly in full to the acquisition costs (see BFH judgment of 10 10 1991 BStBl 1992 Part II, page 239)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "If subsequent acquisition costs are incurred later in the case of a partially paid acquisition, these are not to be divided between the paid and unpaid part of the acquisition"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Rather, they fully increase the assessment basis of Section 10e EStG for the part of the apartment purchased for a fee"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Example: In 1991 the parents transferred a condominium to their son through anticipated inheritance regulation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "The market value of the apartment is 300,000 DM"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "S undertakes to pay his sister an equal opportunity allowance of DM 150,000"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Immediately after the transfer of the apartment, S begins building a winter garden that can be used all year round"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Its production costs amount to 30,000 DM"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "When the apartment was transferred, incidental acquisition costs of DM 10,000 were incurred"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Overall, the condominium is used by S for its own residential purposes"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "For the sake of simplicity, the share of land is DM 0"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Solution: The condominium acquired by S by way of the anticipated inheritance regulation in 1991 is a partially paid purchase transaction"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "S paid his sister acquisition costs of DM 150,000 in the amount of the equal opportunities allowance"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "In relation to the market value of the property (300,000 DM), half of this is a paid and the other half is a purchase transaction free of charge"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "The incidental acquisition costs are directly attributable to the purchase transaction against payment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "The subsequent production costs in the amount of 30,000 DM would not be favored as an extension if strictly considered to a second new property according to \u00a7 10e Paragraph 2 EStG because of the spatial context"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "In these cases, however, there are no concerns about treating these expenses as subsequent production costs, which are nevertheless favored according to \u00a7 10e EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Acquisition costs: 150,000 DM Incidental acquisition costs: 10,000 DM Subsequent acquisition costs: 30,000 DM Total: 190000 DMVI Follow-up property For a follow-up property, Section 10e EStG in its current version at the time of acquisition or manufacture is decisive"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "However, only the percentages of the years remaining from the first object are decisive"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Example: A has claimed deductions for a single-family house built in 1990 and sold again on June 1, 1992, in accordance with Section 10 (1) EStG for the assessment periods 1990 to 1992"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "With a notarized sales contract dated July 1, 1993, he acquires a condominium that he uses for his own residential purposes from the time of purchase"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "A makes use of the subsequent property regulation in accordance with Section 10, Paragraph 4, Clause 4 of the Income Tax Act"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Solution: The new degressive design of \u00a7 10e Abs 1 EStG with the deduction rate of 6 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "affects the subsequent property in the 1993 assessment period"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "The deduction period for the first property spanned the years 1990 to 1992. The basic funding allowed for this was therefore 3 x 5 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": ", at most DM 15,000 each"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "The subsequent property is a property within the meaning of Section 10e, Paragraph 1 of the Income Tax Act in the version of the Tax Amendment Act 1992. Accordingly, the degressive deduction rates are generally to be applied, but the years used for the first property must be taken into account when calculating the percentages"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "This means that the deduction period for the subsequent property includes the years 1993 to 1997 and the remaining deductible amounts from the 4th to the 8th year for the first property"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "The basic funding for the assessment period 1993 is therefore 6 per cent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": ", at most DM 19,800"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "For the years 1994 to 1997, 4 x 5 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "up to a maximum of 16,500 DM each"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "As part of the subsequent property regulation, it may also be possible to claim the extended debt interest deduction in accordance with Section 10e (6a) of the Income Tax Act for the subsequent property"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "For clarification, reference is made in this context to the following example"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Example: S made use of the deductions for a single-family house purchased in 1991 and sold again on June 1, 1993, in accordance with Section 10e, Paragraph 1 of the Income Tax Act for the assessment periods 1991 to 1993"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "In 1992, S built another property, which he used for his own residential purposes after the single-family house was sold in 1993"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "S makes use of the subsequent property regulation in accordance with Section 10e, Paragraph 4, Clause 4 of the Income Tax Act"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "In the individual years from the assessment period 1992 onwards, he pays debt interest of DM 15,000 annually"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Solution: Since the subsequent property is a property within the meaning of Section 10e EStG Paragraph 1 EStG in the version of the Tax Amendment Act 1992, S can in principle claim the debt interest deduction for the property in accordance with Section 10e Paragraph 6 a EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "However, the prerequisite is that the taxpayer claims the deduction amounts for this property in accordance with Section 10e Paragraph 1 or 2 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "A debt interest deduction is therefore ruled out for the assessment period 1992, since the taxpayer has not yet used the subsequent property for his own residential purposes"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "For the assessment period 1993, a debt interest deduction in accordance with \u00a7 10e Paragraph 6 a EStG is also not possible, as the taxpayer still takes advantage of the basic subsidy for the first property according to \u00a7 10e Paragraph 1 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Accordingly, he can only deduct debt interest up to a maximum of DM 12,000 for the 1994 assessment period in accordance with Section 10e (6a) of the Income Tax Act"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "A recovery of the debt interest deduction not used in 1992 according to \u00a7 10e Paragraph 6 a Sentence 2 EStG in the calendar year 1995 is ruled out because in 1992 the conditions for claiming the debt interest deduction according to \u00a7 10e Paragraph 6 a EStG did not exist Taxpayers could not take advantage of the tax relief of \u00a7 10e Abs 1 EStG for the subsequent property"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "VII \u00a7 10e EStG in the case of owners' associations The administrative opinion presented under V 1, Paragraph 2 in my reference order of 18 11 1988 is now outdated (BFH judgment of 12 2 1988 BStBl Part II, page 764 principle of legal jurisdiction over joint property)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "According to section 27 of the BMF letter, the co-owner of a two-family house can claim all of his expenses for the owner-occupied apartment within the framework of Section 10e Paragraph 1 Clause 1 or Paragraph 2 EStG if his co-ownership share is in relation to the value of the apartment used for his own residential purposes Value of the building"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "VIII \u00a7 10e Abs 6 EStG The deductible expenses of a taxpayer according to \u00a7 10e Abs 6 EStG do not include the deductions for wear and tear in accordance with \u00a7 7 EStG, see FG Munich, judgment of 21 5 1992 K 4660/90 NWB Eilnachrichten 1992 p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "351 (exception, however, see para"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "I3: acquisition costs for a heritable building right)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Expenses i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Section 10e (6) of the Income Tax Act only applies if there is a direct connection with the owner-occupied apartment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "A consideration of futile costs such as special expenses is therefore ruled out (Paragraph 56 of the BMF letter, BFH judgment of 17 7 1991 BStBl II page 916)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Expenses for trips to obtain loan offers to finance the or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Self-used residential property to be purchased can be deducted like special expenses if they are directly related to the owner-occupied residential property and if it is a question of financing costs (Section 50 of the BMF letter)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Operating costs (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Property tax and building insurance premiums) can be deducted in the year of payment up to the amount in which they apply to the period up to the first use of the apartment for personal residential purposes"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Reference is made to the statements in Section 54 of the BMF letter"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "According to Section 10e, Paragraph 6 of the Income Tax Act (EStG), expenses can also be deducted that the taxpayer had incurred prior to the first use of an extension or extension of the apartment used for their own residential purposes (Section 61 of the BMF letter)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Expenses related to subsequent production costs are not deductible according to Section 10e, Paragraph 6 of the Income Tax Act"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "If a taxpayer acquires an apartment free of charge, he can reimburse the expenses incurred until moving into the apartment i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Only claim against \u00a7 10e (6) EStG for tax purposes if he is the universal successor and the testator has not previously used the apartment for his own residential purposes"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "In a judgment of 11 3 1992, the BFH, contrary to Section 49 of the BMF letter, takes the view that expenses incurred prior to moving in for the renovation of an apartment used for one's own residential purposes can be deducted according to Section 10e (6) EStG, even in the case of free individual legal succession of the apartment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "This interpretation is doubtful with regard to the wording as well as the meaning and purpose of the provision"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "The judgment is not to be applied beyond the decided individual case, also with regard to other similar proceedings pending at the BFH (BStBl 1992 Part I, page 584)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Comparable legal remedy procedures can continue to be suspended with the consent of the Stpfl (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "In the case of a partially paid acquisition, a differentiated assessment of the tax case is required according to the administrative opinion: Example: A, B and C are in equal parts heirs of their father V, who died in January 01. The inheritance essentially consists of a single-family house (market value DM 450,000, including the reason and land 75,000 DM), which V used for his own residential purposes until his death"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "A takes over the shares of the siblings (market value of the two shares: 300,000 DM, including land and land share 50,000 DM) in July 01 against compensation payments of 75,000 DM each (total"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "150,000 DM)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "After the renovation of the building (construction costs: 12,000 DM), A moved into the house in December 01 and used it for his own residential purposes from then on"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "To finance the compensation payments, A takes out a loan, for which he pays DM 15,000 in debt interest in 01"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Solution: A has become 1/3 universal successor to V."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "The renovation costs of 4,000 DM attributable to this share represent maintenance expenses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "However, they cannot be used as initial costs i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Section 10e (6) of the Income Tax Act (EStG) must be taken into account in a tax-reducing manner, since V had used the single-family house for his own residential purposes until his death (not first-time use, A takes on the legal status of his father)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "A acquired the co-ownership shares of his siblings (2/3 of the property) against payment of DM 150,000 in part for consideration"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "In this respect, he is entitled to the deduction amount according to Section 10e (1) EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "The maximum amount according to \u00a7 10e Abs 1 EStG is not reduced (section 16 of the BMF letter)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "The renovation costs of 4,000 DM (2/3 of 12,000 DM = 8,000 DM, 50% of which are proportionally attributable to the paid acquisition)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": ") are deductible according to \u00a7 10e Abs6 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "The remaining DM 4,000 maintenance expenses are attributable to the portion acquired free of charge and cannot be taken into account in a tax-reducing manner, since A, as the sole legal successor to his siblings, is not entitled to deduct the costs under Section 10e (6) of the Income Tax Act"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "On the other hand, the debt interest paid by A in the amount of DM 15,000 is fully deductible as preliminary costs in accordance with Section 10e (6) of the Income Tax Act (EStG), since it only applies to the part of the single-family home that has been acquired against payment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Calculation of \u00a7 10e EStG: acquisition costs: 150,000 DM"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Land25000 DM125000 DM + 1/2 Land12500 DM = BMG \u00a7 10e EStG137500 DMIX Debt interest deduction according to \u00a7 10e Abs 6 a EStG The definition of debt interest in \u00a7 10e Abs 6 a EStG, like the definition of debt interest in \u00a7 10e Abs 6 EStG, is to be interpreted broadly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "In addition to the normal debt interest, this regulation also includes the damnum and other money-raising costs, such as"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Appraisal, mortgage brokerage, guarantee and allotment fees, financing-related notary fees, loan commissions and commitment interest"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "The ground rent are also to be treated like debt interest"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "The discounted part of a purchase price claim may be"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "can also be taken into account in accordance with Section 10e (6a) of the Income Tax Act"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Example: S acquires a single-family house on 1 3 1992 by way of an anticipated succession from his father in return for payment of an equal opportunity allowance to his sister in the amount of 200,000 DM"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "The purchase price is due in one sum on February 28, 1994"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "The market value of the property is DM 360,000"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Solution: The acquisition of the single-family house in anticipated succession is a partially paid purchase transaction"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "S has acquisition costs within the meaning of \u00a7 10e EStG in the amount of the discounted present value of the equality allowances, since in the present case it is a non-interest-bearing cash benefit with a term of more than one year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Based on the provisions of the Valuation Act, this results in a purchase price of DM 179,690"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "The taxpayer can claim the interest portion of 20,310 DM up to an amount of 12,000 DM in the 1994 assessment period when paying as debt interest in accordance with Section 10e (6a) of the Income Tax Act"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "The provision of \u00a7 10e Paragraph 6 a EStG is only applicable to new buildings, i.e."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": ", the taxpayer must produce the beneficiary property according to Section 10e Paragraph 1 or Paragraph 2 EStG or purchase it by the end of the year of completion"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "The debt interest deduction is generally linked to the actual use of the tax deduction amount according to \u00a7 10e EStG in the respective assessment period"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "However, it is not necessary to claim the full deduction amount"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "However, an exception applies if the taxpayer is only entitled to no deduction due to the income limit in Section 10e (5a) of the Income Tax Act"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "With regard to the application of Section 10e Paragraph 6 a EStG i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "I refer to the remarks on no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "VI 2X depreciation in cases of mixed or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "changed use"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "7 of the Income Tax Act"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "If an apartment previously used for one's own residential purposes is used to generate income i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "EStG related (= change of use), the amount previously to be assessed according to \u00a7 10e EStG can therefore not easily be used as income-related expenses or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "deducted as business expenses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "For the purposes of determining income, the legally permitted depreciation must be determined in these cases"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "The acquisition costs of the land included in the assessment base according to Section 10e (1) EStG cannot be included in the determination of the depreciation assessment basis for depreciation in accordance with Section 7 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "According to section 43, paragraph 6, sentence 3, no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Because of the depreciation method, reference to Section 44 Paragraph 12 Sentence 1 No. 2 EStR"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "In assessment periods in which the apartment is used to generate taxable income after a change in use, a catch-up of depreciation for the previous years is not possible because the statutory depreciation is used for the period of use of an apartment for the owner's own residential purposes and for this period is also not tax deductible in the absence of income (Section 44 Paragraph 12 Sentence 1 No. 2 Sentence 4 EStR)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "If parts of the apartment are not used for their own residential purposes"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Practice rooms, study, cf. \u00a7 10e Paragraph 1 Clause 7 EStG), the acquisition or production costs accruing thereon according to \u00a7 7 Paragraph 4 or Paragraph 5 i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Paragraph 5 a of the Income Tax Act"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "XI Waiver of the value-in-use taxation According to Section 52 (21) sentence 3 EStG, the taxpayer can irrevocably request that the value-in-use taxation be waived for his apartment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "The binding effect of this option already results from the application of the taxpayer in the assessment procedure, not only from the final tax assessment for the first assessment period for which no further value in use is to be recorded (see section II number 4 of the BMF letter of 19 September 1986 BStBl I Page 480 Decree of FM NRW of 19 9 1986 communicated by circular order of 13 10 1986 - S-2225a - 154 - St 16 - 31)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "The application can therefore not be revoked in the appeal procedure (cf. judgment of the FG Bremen of 23 2 1990 EFG 1990 page 528; also: FG M\u00fcnster dated 11 9 1991 Az"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": ": 13 K 2923/90 E (not published))"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "However, for reasons of equity, the tax authorities allow an exception to the irrevocability of the application for the discontinuation of the value-in-use taxation if the tax office divides the expenses into a non-deductible amount and an amount that can be deducted as income from renting and leasing as income-related expenses deviates at the expense of the taxpayer (circular order of the OFD M\u00fcnster from 27 9 1989 - S-2225a - 154 - St 16 - 31 ESt-Nr 74/1989)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "The application in accordance with Section 52, Paragraph 21, Clause 3 of the Income Tax Act can be submitted in accordance with Section II, No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "4 of the BMF letter of 19 September 1986 (op"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": ") until the tax assessment becomes final"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "In the case of a tax assessment (\u00a7 164 AO) that is subject to review, the application is permissible at any time and without restriction, even if the assessment is final"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "In the case of a provisional tax assessment (Section 165 AO), the (subsequent) application is only permissible if the provisionality extends to uncertain facts that are decisive for determining the income from renting and leasing the taxpayer's apartment in accordance with Section 52 (21) sentence 2 EStG are"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "If a building is co-owned by several people and the co-owners each use an apartment of the house corresponding to their co-ownership share, each co-owner can submit the application in accordance with Section 52 (21) sentence 3 EStG alone"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "According to the principle of legal jurisdiction over joint property (see V above), only the co-owner who uses the individual apartment for his own residential purposes fulfills the requirements of Section 52 (21) sentence 2 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "The other co-owners were not assigned any value in use for this apartment in the 1986 assessment period either"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "XII equity measures According to para"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "II 4 sentence 5 of the decree of the Minister of Finance NRW dated 19 September 1986 and section 157 (2) sentence 6 EStR, a taxpayer who has distributed larger maintenance expenses according to \u00a7 82b, \u00a7 82h or \u00a7 82k EStDV can deduct the expenses not yet deducted in one amount deduct in the assessment period for which the value in use is to be recognized for the last time as a result of an option pursuant to Section 52 (21) sentence 3 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "The same applies according to No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "III 1 c of the above"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Decree for \u00a7 21a objects for which the distribution of larger maintenance costs was permitted in accordance with Section 157 (2) sentences 6 10 and 11 of the EStR 1987"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "If the tax assessment of the assessment period for which a value in use is taxed for the last time is already final and the taxpayer has inadvertently paid the maintenance expenses that have not yet been deducted (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "from ignorance of the above"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Instruction) or because he initially wanted to continue the value-in-use taxation, was not asserted in this assessment period, the income tax assessment can be corrected at the request of the taxpayer, since the o"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Provision for the immediate deduction of the remainder of the maintenance expenses not taken into account so far is an equitable measure, which in this respect is a basic notice for the ESt notice"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "The income tax assessment can therefore be changed in accordance with Section 175 (1) No. 1 AO"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "With judgment of 14 11 1990 VII 2386/89 E (not published), the FG M\u00fcnster has maintenance expenses that a taxpayer had in 1985 for his single-family house used for his own residential purposes and spread over five years in accordance with \u00a7 82b EStDV in the calendar year 1987 as subsequent Advertising costs are taken into account in the income from renting and leasing, although the single-family house is exempt from value-in-use taxation by law from the assessment period 1987 under the Home Ownership Promotion Act"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "Since, according to the case law, the elimination of the respective type of income does not preclude the assertion of subsequent business expenses, the distribution of expenses already made, as regulated by law, must continue to apply"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "An appeal against this judgment is pending at the BFH under file number IX R 14/91"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "According to the small transitional regulation of Section 52 (21) sentence 4 EStG, increased deductions according to Section 7b EStG and the extended debt interest deduction according to Section 21a (4) EStG can be deducted as special expenses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "This can lead to income tax disadvantages if the amount of certain income or the total amount of income is taxable (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "with \u00a7\u00a7 10b, 10d, 14a, 18 Abs 4 EStG 1987 24a, 33 46 Abs 2 Nr 1 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "The legislature consciously accepted these far-reaching effects, which were also known when the Home Ownership Promotion Act was passed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "There are therefore no reasons for a different tax assessment for objective reasons of equity"}, {"meta": {"name": "0107122.xml"}, "text": "XIII Tax treatment of building society savings interest reference to the BMF letter dated 28 2 1990 BStBl 1990 I page 124 Income tax, residential property, income tax / wage tax / church tax procedural law / tax code, tax support laws, North Rhine-Westphalia"}]